org.wiredwidgets.cow.server.api.model.v2

Class Loop

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wiredwidgets.cow.server.api.model.v2.Activity
      • org.wiredwidgets.cow.server.api.model.v2.Loop

  • public class Loop
extends Activity
    A Loop contains an Activity and a Task. The Task represents a workflow step in which a decision maker determines whether the Activity should be repeated. A typical use for a Loop structure would be to implement an approval process.

    Java class for Loop complex type.

    The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

     <complexType name="Loop">
   <complexContent>
     <extension base="{http://www.wiredwidgets.org/cow/server/schema/model-v2}Activity">
       <sequence>
         <element ref="{http://www.wiredwidgets.org/cow/server/schema/model-v2}activity"/>
         <element name="loopTask" type="{http://www.wiredwidgets.org/cow/server/schema/model-v2}Task"/>
       </sequence>
       <attribute name="doneName" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" default="Done" />
       <attribute name="repeatName" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" default="Repeat" />
       <attribute name="executionCount" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}integer" />
     </extension>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>
